values:
hey guys! i'm out here in the middle of nowhere, in this valley-desert-extremely small town, Crestone, CO. lol it's really gorgeous though, we're surrounded by these beautiful mountains, the sunsets are amazing [people tell me the sunrises are too, but we all kno i sure as hell havent seen it for myself], and we're so high up it looks like the sky is so much closer, the clouds are gigantic. it looks like if you climb one of the mountains you'd be able to touch the sky. its a little too quiet for me though, and its a little too.. i dunno, not city-ish enough for me. "downtown" is about the size of my thumbnail lol. it's really cute though, very picturesque. is that how you spell picturesque? i have no idea lol. but yes.. i came out here to meet Chalanda Sai Ma. she's a kind of relgious leader that my grandma has been following for a at least 2 years now, i don't remember how long. but yeah, my gramma is totally into her and wanted me to come out here to CO to meet her and go to this youth weekend program. so i did.. it started friday night and ended sunday afternoon. i dont really know what to think about Sai Ma and what she teaches and everything. i expected some crazy hippie people [well, there are a few hippies out here lol but they're ok] or like, a crazy-ass cult or some shit. but it's really not like that. and i thought i was confused before about my religious beliefs? HAH, that was nothing compared to now. i don't know what the fuck to think. all i know is that Sai Ma is not the same as us, there is definitely something different about her, something powerful. and the fact that she's a real person, that i can see her and hear her and touch her.. it just kind of makes all of this slightly more believable. but i dont really know how to explain Sai Ma or her teachings or how she makes me feel. it's something that needs to be experienced in person. but i can definitely say that since spending time with her and talking to her and everything, i am definitely not the same person i was. i definitely want to come back here when Sai Ma is here [she left for France sunday morning]. i think im going to come back maybe for Thanksgiving and def. for that week between Christmas and New Years. i'd come back for all of Christmas vacation, but i want to be there for Leah's real first Christmas. lol last year she was only a few days old, this year will really be her first Christmas. and i cannot miss that. so i want to come back for that, and hopefully there'll be more youth programs next summer. and hopefully the kids that were here for this one will come back because i met some awesome kids. and Aneta, you're coming with me because i really think you'd like it. you'd love it out here and you'd LOVE Sai Ma. and you said that you wanted to try and go to a bunch of different camps and stuff so.. you're coming with me next summer lol. i'll try to call you this week and i can tell you more about it. OH, AND.. almost everyone out here is a vegetarian, so that's a plus right? lol

ALYSHA IS ALIVE lol &hearts;

hmm well idk really what else to say. its only 10:20 here but im really tired. i think im gonna go to bed because everyone else in the house has and i dont like being downstairs alone lol
